Sunday is our Monday! We like to get you ready for the work week by roasting lots of coffee. ‚Å£

We‚Äôve got a bunch of exciting new coffee offerings debuting in this month. For our Dark Nebula, we‚Äôve got a new naturally processed coffee from Brazil Cerrado Mineiro that we‚Äôll be using for our dark roast. It boasts that big body and super smooth acidity that you crave in your dark roast with notes of dark cocoa and sweet caramel covered cherries. ‚Å£
‚Å£
This coffee was grown by Marcelo Assis Nogueira. Marcelo‚Äôs passion for coffee comes from his father, a rural worker who found coffee culture as a basis to support his family. This region is recognized internationally for producing some beautiful high quality coffees and we‚Äôre stoked to continue to source beautiful Brazilian coffees for our dark roast from this region. ‚Å£

When the coffee is just that good üòç Ally Coffee (one of our green coffee importers @allycoffee) sent us samples of this coffee from Thailand and we were blown away by how it shined on the cupping table with notes of pear and dark chocolate. We roasted it more medium to give it a rich body and more sweetness, balancing out its mellow acidity. ‚Å£
‚Å£
The people who grew this coffee are truly amazing too... on average they‚Äôre 25-35 years of age. Coffee farming is profitable and attractive to these young entrepreneurs due to opium eradication and subsequent reforestation in the area. Chiang-Rai is located in North Eastern Thailand where the coffee is grown high in the mountains. The farmers take their coffee to the Beanspire Coffee Mill that‚Äôs equipped to help farmer‚Äôs finish processing their coffee and dry it on bamboo raised beds. They also connect farmers to the international specialty coffee market (head to their IG to see @beanspirecoffee).‚Å£
‚Å£
We‚Äôre so excited to share this beautiful coffee from Thailand with you! Just put it up on our website, we have it on the shelves and we‚Äôre serving it by the cup on our pour over bar.‚Å£
‚Å£

Fresh coffee from Oaxaca, Mexico is online and on the shelves! This lot was farmed by a group in the town of Santiago-Yaitepec. ‚Å£
‚Å£
In Pluma Hidalgo, a sub-region of Oaxaca, majority of the coffee is grown by small holder farmers. Over the past 80-100 years, farmers were blending all of their coffees together into one large bulk lot of coffee. Now, farmers are realizing that they can actually make more money by keeping the lots separate.‚Å£
‚Å£
This Mexican coffee is roasted more medium with creamy milk chocolate notes, a smooth acidity and brown sugar sweetness. ‚Å£
‚Å£
‚Å£

It‚Äôs cute and festive but it‚Äôs also delicious and good for you! Our Beet Latte is a combination of organic chai spices + beet root powder, a little bit of our house made vanilla syrup and steamed milk.‚Å£
‚Å£
Beet root powder contains loads of antioxidants, fiber, calcium, iron, potassium and other nutrients. Most notably, beets are naturally rich in nitrates that help improve blood flow, blood pressure and improve circulation. This is what gives you a nice little energy boost after your beet latte without any added caffeine.‚Å£

Some behind the scenes from @brownbarnfilms of Casey (our head roaster and co-owner) and Neil (our roaster stage) cupping coffees together.‚Å£
‚Å£
Coffee is a chain of people, one by one connecting you to your morning brew. We understand our role is integral - we take the culmination of many hard working hands and feel a responsibility to present each coffee and tell its story. ‚Å£
‚Å£
By working with stand up importers like Red Fox @redfoxcoffeemerchants , we can make careful choices about which coffees we buy not just based on the score of the coffee. We get to know the farmers and their growing practices, their community and their struggles. We get to see how much of our dollar is going to them and can make sure that we‚Äôre buying coffees based on our values. ‚Å£
‚Å£
After we select a coffee to buy, we start working to dial in the roast profile. We roast, cup and repeat to develop the coffee‚Äôs inherent flavor profile. We take great pride in this process and never treat two coffees the same, because they aren‚Äôt!‚Å£
‚Å£
The coffee that ultimately ends up in your cup is the result of many hands coming together from all across the world. That is truly amazing! It‚Äôs easy to enjoy a coffee now a days (I mean, it‚Äôs literally everywhere) but it‚Äôs important to remember where it came from and purchase coffee with intention. There is a greater industry behind it all, and if we want coffee to be sustainable and farmer‚Äôs to keep growing it, we‚Äôve got to be aware of where it‚Äôs coming from first. ‚Å£
‚Å£

#throwbackthursday to this day in 2017 - we opened our doors on Main Street in Sebastopol. Photos from our dear friend and photographer @christophersturm‚Å£
‚Å£
We had 3 team members, Casey and I (Danielle) worked open-close fueled by mostly coffee and burritos. A few days later heavy rains came, flooded hwy 12 and we lost power. We were sooo tired, it was welcomed... like the universe was telling us we needed rest and more help! ‚Å£
‚Å£
From there we built our team and our community, slowly but surely, the only way we know how. Today we have 17! amazing team members, we‚Äôre preparing to expand and DOUBLE our cafe space, and best of all, we have a buzzing community of people we now call friends. ‚Å£
‚Å£
We love you all so much! Your support allows us to serve delicious food and drinks, offer a community gathering space and foster a positive and supportive team of individuals who look forward to brewing your coffee every single day. ‚Å£
We‚Äôre able to support other like-minded local small businesses, our schools, food banks, our environment, many community non-profit organizations and coffee farmer‚Äôs all over the world. That is the real dream come true. ‚Å£
‚Å£
Tuesday, January 14th we‚Äôll be celebrating turning 3 ü•≥ with complimentary cupcakes from @red_bird_bakery around 11 AM, a BIG merch sale and a good ol birthday party. You‚Äôre all invited so we can celebrate what we‚Äôve built together! THANK YOU! Let‚Äôs make this year the best one yet. ‚Å£
‚Å£
